Banks deduct **TDS on FD interest** at 10% when interest income exceeds ₹40,000 per year (₹50,000 for senior citizens) from a single bank. If you have not submitted your PAN, TDS is deducted at 20%. You can claim a refund of excess TDS when filing your ITR if your total tax liability is lower.
